data.name: Text_ProjectStructure.Text
data.value:
The C# WinForms project is organized into three main components:
**1. Helpers:**
- **Purpose:** Contains reusable classes and functions accessible across all project modules. - *Folders in helper Folder:** -- - *`CodeGeneration` -- The CodeGeneration has : A - BasicCodeGenerator is Class For : write and read the c# Sourcecode Tools with using Roslyn B - CodeProccessingHelper is Class For : Extract Elements and Classes C - ProjectAnalyzer is Class For : GetNamespaces and AnalyzeProject of c# sourcecode Project ---- - *`DataOperations` -- The DataOperations has two Folders: -1 -Classes ---DatabaseConnection ---DatabaseSchemaOperations ---DataOperations ---FilteringOperatin ---PagingOperations ---SortingOperations
-2 -Interface ---IDatabaseConnection ---IDatabaseSchemaOperations ---IDataOperations ---IFilteringOperatin ---IPagingOperations ---ISortingOperations - *`JsonFiles` - *`Settings` - *`Utils`
**2. Modules:**
- **Purpose:** Represents the primary functional areas of the application. - **Structure:** Each module consists of five folders: - **Models:** Data structures representing entities within the module. - **Services:** Business logic and operations related to the module. - **Interfaces:** Contracts for interactions between components. - **Views:** User interface elements associated with the module. - **SoulControls:** Custom-built controls for enhanced UI/UX. - **Examples:** `AiChat`, `ProjectManagement`, `PersonalContacts`.
**3. SoulCenterGeneral:**
- **Purpose:** Houses core application functionalities and overall project operations. - **Structure:** Mirrors the five-folder structure of modules: - **Models:** Core data structures used throughout the application. - **Services:** Centralized services accessible to all modules. - **Interfaces:** Global interfaces defining communication contracts. - **Views:** Main application views (e.g., main dashboard, settings). - **SoulControls:** Custom controls utilized across the application.
